cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new neural network architecture for model-free reinforcement learning. It also involves training an RL agent to outperform the state-of-the-art on the Atari 2600 domain, which is a common benchmark for machine learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing an RL agent that can learn to make decisions in an environment. The use of convolutional networks and auto-encoders also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively. Finally, the paper may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as RL is a common technique used in robotics for learning control policies.
